[thinking] In Java 17, setting the SecurityManager is allowed with a warning. But in Java 18 and onward, calling System::setSecurityManager throws an UnsupportedOperationException unless "allow" is specified. So, existing tests have a helper method called installSecurityManager that catches the UnsupportedOperationException and returns false. This means they might skip assertions if the SecurityManager isn't installed properly. I need to keep this in mind when setting up tests and handling security configurations.
