[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering SecurityManager settings**\n\nI need to consider whether generated tests should cover the optional security-manager path and whether to set or restore the system property in the test. If there's no action, maybe I should leave the agent_guidance empty to avoid confusion. The user mentioned setting environment variables for sys props, so if there's no required setup, I might leave that as an empty string. I should be confident in my handling of this, especially since there might be issues with JDK 25 removing the SecurityManager entirely.\n\n**Recalling Java SecurityManager behavior**\n\nIn Java 17, setting the SecurityManager is allowed with a warning. But in Java 18 and onward, calling System::setSecurityManager throws an UnsupportedOperationException unless \"allow\" is specified. So, existing tests have a helper method called installSecurityManager that catches the UnsupportedOperationException and returns false. This means they might skip assertions if the SecurityManager isn't installed properly. I need to keep this in mind when setting up tests and handling security configurations.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_00b1f8d38986a021016a4288dbdb488197b24f70436e8385a4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQojm7AkMWTjk_-Wc6lfuqTkgVCDVi9LatV_6rD2V3aHL8qAA3T6jmSPOMIptx4XY5xguBRrzmhJaLgRPoZosNR0QuTYQa8T-dsM94ONKwmwm5SRBCWSsmOn_KsNbTh8V3sCN2kYHgHYaDvlyl-q7ba9Gqn6bksQmQbxL7nmwR_PphUMCUUgJGYvIzWpaZMONSO2LrSf3PVyQTeKNfV7yd1rzCYy_TuEzOXoFdYerIPGb7XIQ4rUltr_pDS-HtsclDrlfrRvWhqh5Q0xD7ZAG-bmzEwdYgYnNKoLcWaFMRI8C55SY-Auc3LW2cf8VKwiV5jXjObTgNRjKSh-qsOt3lenXtUjJ8XAinAwvO-PvJl7mcwHr16fYnZwIVGvY18BocAmtmDFFrWKsxwm1V9DadZ-xeUur58jrvOxIK1O_QQBKi-HxwlTasDDIFTGLk2csfzIf-PuXG74xsC8FTgJMGBARoStXtrCjz-6BRytzMgpoTz8FdoFBtjJUkAgeUpQBnYTNWLmrAhsxm16cyKBxLLf-O_ARlaEaxyy8SwPponMCbfYXLLosybKrUeBx0Y_hf8AdRwV6ESP0Vv0LxoLH59oZyhXRlXXsHgwUQf